{
  "query": "What is the evidence base for the effectiveness of creating large protrusions or ridges (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures?",
  "relevant_summary": "There is currently no evidence base for the effectiveness of creating large protrusions (>50 mm) or large ridges/ledges (>50 mm) on subtidal artificial structures. No studies were found that directly evaluated these interventions during comprehensive literature searches. For small protrusions (1-50 mm), one controlled study in Japan found mixed effects on macroalgal abundance depending on the species. For natural rocky reef topography, one replicated, randomized, controlled study in Italy found that this intervention did not increase the abundance of juvenile canopy macroalgae regardless of topography depth. The complete lack of studies examining large protrusions and ridges means there is no evidence to indicate whether these interventions have any desirable or harmful effects on biodiversity.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3443",
    "3445",
    "3453",
    "3446"
  ]
}

